# 2. イン京都！

Class Representative: Okay, we'll be breaking into our groups now! Then, find the bus associated with your respective tour!
Rui: Two and a half hours by bullet train... But we're finally here.
Miyake: Guys! The bus for the temples and shrines tour is this way!
Hayashi: Oh, we get to start with Kinkaku-ji Temple!
Taniyama: I can't wait! Alright, let's go!
Miyake: Whoa! I can't believe it's actually golden!
Hayashi: Kinkaku-ji, the Temple of the Golden Pavilion. Its official name is apparently Hokuzan Rokuon Zenji Temple, and it's supposed to evoke a sort of paradise on earth...
Taniyama: Yeah, I guess you'd only see a golden temple in a place like that...
Rui: Hehehehe.
Miyake: What's up, Kamishiro? You seem pretty happy about something...
Rui: Oh, I was just imagining what it'd be like to use this temple as a stage. It'd be quite extravagant, no...?
Rui: I can see it already. It's the last remaining haven on the planet, and it explodes during the final scene.
Miyake: What?! You want it to explode?!
Hayashi: Whoa... He really is the Explosive Mad Scientist. I'd never think of something like that.
Taniyama: Hmm... As inappropriate as that sounds, watching this temple explode does seem kinda fun!
Rui: Ah, you think so too?
Taniyama: Yeah, I wanna see it happen since I love it when stuff explodes during movies!
Rui: Oh, I guess great minds do think alike.
Hayashi: But what would that story be about?
Rui: Well, there are a few novels with Kinkaku-ji Temple in it, but this story would be nothing like any of those...
Rui: My story would likely fall under science fiction. A golden temple representing a paradise where the masses flock... Yes, that's not a bad start...
Miyake: Hehe...
Rui: Ah, pardon me... I couldn't help but think out loud.
Miyake: No, that's all good.
Miyake: I can tell that you really love coming up with shows, Kamishiro.
Rui: Hehe... To be fair, I get so overzealous sometimes that I lose sight of the world around me.
Hayashi: Hmm... So, what's wrong with that?
Rui: What?
Taniyama: Yeah! I think it's great that you're so passionate about something!
Taniyama: Just look at my favorite anime director. He became able to come up with these amazing works because he was so obsessed with drawing scenes where buildings collapse and stuff. I think you're like him, Kamishiro!
Hayashi: Oh, but if you're about to miss the bus or something because you spaced out, we'll have to drag you by the scruff of your neck.
Taniyama: How? Kamishiro's way too tall for that. We could maybe do that to Miyake since he's so skinny.
Miyake: What?! There's no way you could! Right, Kamishiro?!
Rui: Hehehe... It may be fun to test that theory out later.
Miyake: Whaaat?!
Miyake: This is a shrine dedicated to a deity of education. Oh, one of the wish placards says, “I'm gonna get accepted!”
Hayashi: *Sigh* Entrance exams are the last thing I wanna think about...
Taniyama: In that sense, Kamishiro, you're really lucky since you always score super high on tests and stuff. I bet you won't have to work very hard to get into most schools.
Rui: Yes, which means... I'll be able to focus on my shows instead of having to worry about exams.
Taniyama: N-No fair! You could be a little more modest!
Rui: Haha. I only speak the truth.
Rui: Ah, this must be a traditional rock garden. It's much more beautiful than in the pictures.
Rui: The boulders represent islands and the lines in the sand represent waves in the water. This must've been how the people of old depicted otherworldly realms.
Miyake: Yeah, that's kinda cool when you put it that way. This place is so calm and sooth—
Taniyama: A-A-Achoo!!!
Miyake: Whoa!
Hayashi: Hey, so much for calm and soothing!
Rui: Haha...! That did sort of turn this place's atmosphere on its head.
Rui: *Sigh* That hot spring was very refreshing.
Miyake: Yeah. But we're probably gonna work up a sweat again because it's so hot out today.
Rui: Ah, I recommend using one of these.
Miyake: Oh, it's a handheld fan...?
Rui: Yes, it is. But it doesn't just blow air. When you press this switch...
Miyake: Whoa! What's it blowing out?! Is this...snow?!
Rui: It's based on an old device that I made for a show when I was looking for a way to make it snow. I succeeded at miniaturizing it, and decided to bring it along since I saw that it was going to be warm here.
Miyake: That's incredible, Kamishiro...! You really are a wiz with gadgets!
Taniyama: Man, that hot spring felt great! Oh, Miyake, you guys are back already?
Hayashi: We should probably start getting our beds ready... But it seems like a waste to go to sleep now. Wanna play something?
Rui: Then, how about cards...?
Hayashi: Ah, a time-honored school trip tradition!
Taniyama: Oh, let's make things interesting! The loser has to...go outside and buy juice from a vending machine somewhere!
Rui: I see. A game of cards with a little twist...
Miyake: But we're not supposed to leave after dark. What if the teachers find out?
Taniyama: Don't be such a goody two-shoes! That's the best part of it!
Rui: Hehe. I agree. That does sound like fun.
Miyake: You're on their side, Kamishiro...?!
Hayashi: Alright, that settles that! You guys ready to play?
Rui: Yeah, let's get started!
Hayashi: A pair of kings! No one's gonna top that...!
Rui: I can. A pair of aces. That's it for me.
Miyake: Whaaat?! You're the president, Kamishiro?!
Taniyama: No...! You didn't cheat, did you?!
Rui: Hehe. Who knows?
Hayashi: I was so sure I'd win... At least I get to be vice president again. Done.
Taniyama: No... At this rate, I'm gonna be forced to go buy juice...! I've gotta turn this around somehow...
Rui: Hm? Is someone outside our door?
Tsukasa's Voice: Rui, are you there?!
Rui: Ah, Tsukasa, is that you?
Taniyama: Oh, it's Weirdo One!
Hayashi: What's up, Tenma?
Tsukasa: I came to see what you're up to... But good! You seem to be behaving yourself!
Rui: Hm? What do you mean?
Tsukasa: I was stopped by one of the teachers while I was making my way over to the baths.
Tsukasa: They asked, “Your partner in crime isn't up to anything, is he?” As much as I hate being treated like one of the usual suspects, I stopped by just to make sure.
Tsukasa: However, you seem to just be playing an ordinary game of cards! All's quiet here!
Tsukasa: Now, if you'll excuse me...
Taniyama: Oh, Tenma, wait up...! Wanna play with us?
Tsukasa: Yes, a game of cards sounds like fun! What were you playing just now?
Miyake: Oh, we were playing President.
Tsukasa: Ah, I'm quite good at that! You shall see why I'm called President Tsukasa!
Taniyama: Nice, Tsukasa's in! That means our initial bet's off since we're starting over!
Miyake: What?! How's that fair?!
Rui: I don't mind.
Rui: We have a bet in place where the person who finished last the most times after five rounds has to go get juice.
Tsukasa: Hah hah hah! I am a future star! “Last” is not a part of my vocabulary!
Rui: Ah, I think I know where this is going.
Tsukasa: So, let's begin!
Tsukasa: Nooo! I'm the beggar again?! How?!
Taniyama: Awesome! Not last! Alright, Tenma, you're getting juice for us!
Hayashi: I can't believe how quickly that came back around...
Tsukasa: Grr...! As frustrating as this is, I must admit defeat...! I'll go get them now!
Rui: Would you like me to go with you, Tsukasa?
Tsukasa: Hm? Why's that? Won't we stand out if we go together?
Rui: Oh, I want to see your walk of sh— I mean, see you embark on this brave endeavor.
Tsukasa: Argh! You're enjoying this, aren't you?!
Hayashi: I say go. It'll be more interesting that way.
Taniyama: Yeah! I mean, everyone's been wondering if the Weirdo Wombo Combo's gonna try to pull something during this trip!
Tsukasa: Don't encourage him! Also, Rui, quit trying to follow me!
Rui: Hehehehe...
Tsukasa: No, stop laughing! And quit following me!
Miyake: Hehe... Things really are fun when these two are together.
